DoubleCharacteristic.name: MPD
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:15] Maximum potential difference between surface and underlying conductor before a discharge occurs.

DoubleCharacteristic.name: RPN2
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:9] Range parameter n2 [-].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: PEY
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:12] Photoelectron current for normally incident sunlight [A/m2 at 1 AU].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: SEY
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:10] Secondary electron yield due to impact of 1 keV protons [-].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: SRE
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:13] Surface resistivity [ohm].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: RPN1
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:7] Range parameter n1 [-].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: DMT
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:1] UNUSED. Please use MatThickness characteristic in the 'Macroscopic Characteristics' property in place of.

DoubleCharacteristic.name: RDC
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:0] Relative dielectric constant [-] (keep it positive even though irrelevant for a conductor).

DoubleCharacteristic.name: BUC
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:2] Bulk conductivity [ohm-1.m-1], must be set negative if a conductor (in place of infinite for a perfect conductor).

DoubleCharacteristic.name: MAD
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:18] Material density [kg/m3]

DoubleCharacteristic.name: PEE
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:5] Primary electron energy that produces maximum (SEE) yield [keV].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: RCC
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:16] Radiation induced conductivity coefficient K [ohm-1.m-1] in the law K*(rate/rate0)^D, with rate0 = 1 Rad/s (TBC), (or equivalently with no rate0 coefficient and rate expressed in Rad/s).

DoubleCharacteristic.name: RPR2
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:8] Range parameter r2 [Angstrom].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: RPR1
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:6] Range parameter r1 [Angstrom] in the range expression r1 (E/E0)^n1 + r2 (E/E0)^n2, with E0 = 1 kEv (or equivalently with no E0 coefficient and E expressed in keV).

DoubleCharacteristic.name: ATN
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:3] Atomic number [-].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: MAP
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:14] Maximum (absolute) potential attainable before a discharge occurs.

DoubleCharacteristic.name: MSEY
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:4] Maximum secondary electron emission (SEE) yield for electron impact [-].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: RCP
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:17] Radiation induced conductivity power (D) [-].

DoubleCharacteristic.name: IPE
DoubleCharacteristic.description: [param:11] Incident proton energy that produces maximum secondaryelectron yield [keV].
